Faction Benefits Quick Reference
Imperial Legion (Defense & Containment)
vs. Rahgot's Plague (Tier 3): Quarantine Protocol - plague cannot spread through hold
vs. Vokun's Assaults (Tier 2): Early Warning - forts cannot be surprised, reinforcements arrive
Stormcloaks (Offense & Disruption)
vs. Nahkriin's Sabotage (Tier 1): Tomb-Wardens - false flag operations automatically fail
vs. Marching Armies (Tier 2/4): Guerrilla Tactics - postpone next Dragon Cult Clock advancement by 1 session

Final GM Philosophy
This clock exists to create meaningful choice under pressure. The players will agonize over their decision. That's the point. But whichever side they choose (or if they broker peace), they are taking action against chaos and forging order from the void.
Remember: There is no perfect choice. Both factions are flawed. Both offer strategic value. The only wrong choice is to choose nothing and let Skyrim burn while remaining "above it all."
The anguish is the point. The choice is the mechanism. Unity is the goal.


